    "Let btr denote the baby-step training.",
    "The Input: Set1: Normal SWaT dataset (NSD).",
    "Set2: Sensor label s and time index i. Set3: Sensors-actuators relationship graph RG.",
    "Output: The state bounds [LB, UB] for the sensor.",
    "Def NearestNeighbors(s, RG): return nearestActsList:= FindInOutSensorEdges(s) Def SwitchBoardState(i, s, actstate, RG): nnActs:= NearestNeighbors(s, RG) sbFlag:= isMember(actstate, nnActs) if sbFlag==True: return sb:= Concat(nnActs) else: return -1 Def DatasetDiff(NSD, s): Table 2: An example normal (training) dataset for sensor LIT101 and its nn-actuators."
